<h1>CGI Programming OpenFAQ</h1>
	<h1>Application to Write Articles</h1>
	You must provide your email address. When you do, you 
	will be <strong>emailed a password</strong> which you
	will use when adding or updating articles. This is done
	in order to provide the OpenFAQ with a modest degree of
	credibility, cutting down greatly on spam and other
	abuses of this free service. <strong>If you do not wish 
	to provide your email address, you will not be able to 
	participate.  Sorry for any inconvenience.</strong>
	<p>
	<strong>
	ALL MATERIALS ARE REVIEWED BY THE MODERATOR BEFORE
	THEY APPEAR TO THE PUBLIC. IF YOU ARE ABOUT TO SPAM,
	DON'T BOTHER.
	<p>
	THE MAINTAINER HAS THE FINAL SAY IN ACCEPTING AND/OR
	EDITING ARTICLES. IF YOU DO NOT LIKE THE MAINTAINER'S
	POLICIES, SET UP YOUR OWN OPENFAQ.
	<p>
	ALL MATERIALS YOU SUBMIT ARE COVERED BY THE GNU
	PUBLIC LICENSE. IF YOU DO NOT WISH TO MAKE YOUR
	CONTRIBUTIONS FREELY REPRODUCIBLE BY ALL, WITHOUT FEE,
	OR YOU DO NOT OWN THE COPYRIGHT ON YOUR MATERIALS,
	DO NOT SUBMIT THEM. FILLING OUT THIS APPLICATION
	SIGNIFIES ACCEPTANCE OF THESE TERMS.
	</strong>
	<p>
	Please provide your email address and the name your 
	articles should be attributed to at this time. 
	Names should not contain spaces or other non-alpha
	characters (letters, underscores and digits are OK).
	<p>
	<form action="http://www.boutell.com/openfaq/cgi/apply.cgi/applysubmit" method=POST>
	<input name="name">Your Name (NO SPACES!)<br>
	<input name="email">Your Email Address<br>
	<input type=submit value="Apply Now">
	</form>
